  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Toss asparagus with olive oil, cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper on a baking sheet. Roast for 12-15 minutes or until tender.",
    "While asparagus is roasting, cook quinoa according to package instructions.",
    "In a small pan, heat lemon juice and garlic over low heat until fragrant.",
    "To assemble bowls, divide cooked quinoa among bowls, then top with roasted asparagus, chopped parsley, feta cheese, and a dollop of tahini sauce.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh mint and a sprinkle of sumac, if using.",
    "Serve immediately, or refrigerate for up to 3 days and reheat as needed."
